{"title":"Amulet of resist slowing","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Amulet_of_resist_slowing","type":"markdown","data":"***Obsolete**: This article refers to an aspect of the game which has been removed. It is retained for historical reference only.*\n\nThe **amulet of resist slowing** prevents the player from receiving the [slow](/Slow \"Slow\") status effect. In addition, it extended the duration of [haste](/Haste \"Haste\") effects (it resists you from slowing down from hasted speed).\n\n## Desirability\n\nFor most characters, it's better than nothing. For casters, its around on par with an [amulet of clarity](/Amulet_of_clarity \"Amulet of clarity\"). Any character can appreciate the extension of haste, though you'll likely prefer an amulet of conservation or resist mutation by the lategame.\n\nA godsend for [Berserkers](/Berserker \"Berserker\"), since it prevents the slow after berserking. You'll still have to worry about [paralysis](/Paralysis \"Paralysis\"), at least if [Trog](/Trog \"Trog\") piety isn't high enough.\n\n## History\n\n- The amulet of resist slowing was replaced with the [amulet of stasis](/Amulet_of_stasis \"Amulet of stasis\") in [0.6](/0.6 \"0.6\").\n- In very ancient versions of Crawl, these were known as **amulets of maintain speed**.\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Amulet of resist slowing - CrawlWiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Amulet_of_resist_slowing\",\"wgTitle\":\"Amulet of resist slowing\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":71841,\"wgRevisionId\":71841,\"wgArticleId\":6515,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":n